                <h1>Discovering Subaru: A Journey Through History</h1>
                <p>Subaru, founded in 1953, emerged as a pioneer in all-wheel-drive technology and boxer engine design. Originally a division of Fuji Heavy Industries, it introduced its first car, the Subaru 360, in 1954. Over the decades, Subaru gained a reputation for durability and performance, particularly in rally racing, appealing to adventure-seekers worldwide.</p>
